#UI_UX_Principles

## Seven Foundational UI Design Principles

### 1. Hierarchy Implementation
**Technical Requirements:**
- Use Tailwind's typography scale systematically: `text-xs` to `text-6xl`
- Implement semantic heading structure (h1-h6) with consistent visual hierarchy
- Apply `font-weight` classes strategically: `font-light`, `font-normal`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold`
- Use `space-y-*` and `space-x-*` utilities for consistent spacing
- Implement visual hierarchy through color contrast: `text-primary`, `text-secondary`, `text-muted-foreground`

**Code Pattern:**
```tsx
// Primary action - highest hierarchy
<Button size="lg" className="text-lg font-semibold">
// Secondary content - lower hierarchy  
<p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
```
### 2. Consistency Standards
**Design System Requirements:**
- Create centralized theme configuration in `tailwind.config.js`
- Use shadcn/ui's theming system for consistent component behavior
- Implement consistent spacing scale: `4px` base unit (Tailwind's default)
- Maintain consistent border radius: `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`
- Use consistent animation timing: `transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out`

**Component Standardization:**
```tsx
// Consistent button patterns
const buttonVariants = {
  primary: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
  secondary: "bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80",
  // All buttons use consistent padding, typography, and transitions
}
```

### 3. Progressive Disclosure
**Implementation Strategy:**
- Use shadcn/ui components and leverage rules from shadcn.mdc
- Use https://tailark.com/  or https://ui.aceternity.com/components for react Components**
- Utilize `Collapsible` components for optional information
- Create contextual help with `Popover` and `Tooltip` components
- Always show progress indicators for multi-step processes

**Navigation Pattern:**
```tsx
<Stepper currentStep={step} totalSteps={totalSteps} />
<Progress value={completionPercentage} />
```

### 4. Strategic Contrast
**Color System Implementation:**
- Use Tailwind's color palette with semantic naming
- Implement proper contrast ratios for accessibility (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text)
- Create visual emphasis through background colors: `bg-primary`, `bg-destructive`, `bg-secondary`
- Use border contrast for subtle emphasis: `border-primary/20`

**Attention-Grabbing Elements:**
```tsx
// Critical actions use high contrast
<Button variant="destructive" className="bg-red-600 text-white">
  Delete Account
</Button>
// Secondary actions use subtle contrast
<Button variant="ghost" className="text-muted-foreground">
  Cancel
</Button>
```

### 5. Accessibility Compliance
**WCAG 2.1 AA Standards:**
- All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable
- Implement proper ARIA labels and roles
- Ensure color contrast ratios meet standards
- Provide alternative text for images and icons
- Use semantic HTML elements appropriately
- Support screen readers with proper heading structure

**Implementation Requirements:**
```tsx
// Proper semantic structure
<main role="main">
  <h1 className="sr-only">Page Title</h1>
  <Button 
    aria-label="Close dialog"
    className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary"
  >
```

### 6. Proximity Principles
**Layout Patterns:**
- Group related elements using Flexbox and Grid layouts
- Use consistent spacing between related elements: `gap-2`, `gap-4`, `gap-6`
- Implement card-based layouts for content grouping
- Utilize whitespace effectively with `space-y-*` utilities
- Create visual relationships through container grouping

**Grouping Strategy:**
```tsx
<Card className="p-6 space-y-4">
  {/* Related elements grouped together */}
  <div className="flex gap-2">
    <PlayButton />
    <PauseButton />
    <SkipButton />
  </div>
  {/* Unrelated actions separated */}
  <div className="pt-4 border-t">
    <ExitButton />
  </div>
</Card>
```

### 7. Alignment System
**Grid-Based Layout:**
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for precise alignment
- Implement consistent grid system using Tailwind's grid utilities
- Maintain vertical rhythm with consistent line heights
- Use `items-center`, `justify-center`, `items-start` for proper alignment
- Create visual balance through symmetrical layouts